	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102214006554592>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=2274&mid=102214006554592>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2274&mid=102214006554592>rare drops</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2274&mid=102214006554592#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, May 23rd 3:57 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=158403><span id= >dargoth</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have been in this dungeon for over 50 hours in total, camping in rotation Rathyl, Najena and occasionally Drezlna (or (hardcore) Webmistress with others !). <br><br>As a level 35 magician you can do any two of these complete spawn sets in solo with FM and DS'd focused earth pet. I would suggest that the xp is ok (they are all dark blue to me xcpt webmistress yellow) and the loot and cash is very good indeed. Gypsy and druid vendors nearby in lava... <br><br>The only problem is that I have been camping for the tome and Rathyl's 8 slot pack all this time with no success with either (and about 30 kills of each mob at least). <br><br>I think najena spawns about 1/3 of the time in all and rathyl about 1/2 the time instead of their PH's. <br><br>Magicians go to this zone ) - get your focus items, pages of mastery and xp, loot and a fun place to solo with your pet or group for faster rotation through dungeon... <br><br>If you are in solo, the best place bar none for getting focus items, pages of elemental mastery for epic and sellable / nice drops + ok xp at this level is rathyls room and surrounding area. Neighbouring darkbones and Rathyl's magician protectors drop a lot more focus stuff than anywhere else in dungeon plus you might get a pack / pouch / bracers / ekeros drop to sell to a monk ) <br><br>If you sit and camp in one spot you are less likely to get any kind of decent drop in my experience, let the spawns pop and fully buff 1st for more chance I think. However, if you cant handle a whole room's worth on FM, then space out the kills when you first go in, they will pop with the same spacing ! Always get necro / magician protectors 1st cos when they pop again you can nuke them before they can buff / summon pets.<br><br>I just want the drops to come my way sometime :( <br><br>Dargoth Nethelorien (35 Magician on AB). <br><br>/auc WTB Najena's Tome and Rathyl's Pack on Antonius Bayle PST :)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu May 23 04:03:38 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
