	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84649><span id=Scholar>Troodon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>699 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've noticed that the population of the Old World dungeons have gone down dramatically since Kunark and Velious came out.&nbsp;&nbsp;It used to be that a level 1 could safely wander all the way across Upper and Lower Guk since so many people were camping the place, anything would be immediately attacked upon spawning.<br><br>Najena's become a real ghost town.  Seems anybody in there is either camping magicians to get the rare page for the mage epic, or Ekeros for the FP monks' red sash.  Rathyl drops a nice weight reducing pack, but very rarely, and people usually try to acquire one elsewhere.  Anyway, nobody fights in here just for experience, because the spawn rate is so slow.  Anybody in here is after a specific piece of loot, then they get out.<br><br>As for the flowing black robe, this used to be a popular item that sold well.  But with all the much better, and more common, caster robes coming in from Velious, the FBR doesn't sell well anymore, at least not for what would be a significant amount to the level of person that can kill Najena.  The person who helped me take out Najena just gave the FBR away to a newbie caster.</p>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu Twoflower, Level 55 Iksar Monk, Solusek Ro<br><br>My profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426</a></td></td></tr>
